  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim is to develop and validate a new brief and accurate case-finding instrument for
      dementia and cognitive impairment - BASIC
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The case-finding instrument consists of four components: a. patient-directed questions, b.
      supermarket fluency, c. category-cued Memory Test, d. informant-directed questions.

      The data collection was carried out at five outpatient memory clinics in Denmark
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
